<h3>Jobs</h3>
<p>Accept Jobs to receive money. The job's difficulty vary depending on the job's type. The more difficult a job is, the higher it will be rewarded, but it is also harder to complete. The higher your skills, the faster a job can be completed. You cannot accept a job while you are performing an action.</p>
<% if @jobs.present? %>
  <table border="0" class="table table-condensed" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
    <tr>
      <th>Job Type</th>
      <th>Duration</th>
      <th style="text-align: right;">Reward</th>
      <th>&nbsp;</th>
    </tr>
  <% @jobs.each do |job| %>
      <td><%= job.title %></td>
      <td><%= short_time(job.duration_for(current_user)) %></td>
      <td class="amount"><%= number_to_currency(job.reward, :format => "%n %u") %></td>
      <td>
      <% if current_user.has_incomplete_actions? %>
        <span class="deactivated">Action pending</span>
      <% else %>
        <%= link_to "accept", accept_job_path(job.id), :class => "btn btn-primary" %></td>
      <% end %>
    </tr>
    <% end %>
  </table>
<% else %>
  There are currently no jobs available. Check back later!
<% end %>